<anchor id="disptask_8h_1disptask"/> <simplesect kind="par"><title>Detailed Description </title><para>Calculation of displacement values based on the recorded acceleration data in z-direction. The implementation of this class is based on the calculation done by <ulink url="https://endaq.com/pages/vibration-shock-analysis-software-vibrationdata-toolbox?utm_source=youtube&amp;utm_medium=video&amp;utm_campaign=download-software&amp;utm_content=how-to-calculate-velocity-from-acceleration-data-to-vibrationdata-toolbox">enDAQ VibrationData Toolbox Version 13.3 by Tom Irvine</ulink>. To reprodice the calculation results of the toolbox a small python script has been developed which was used as the base of the implementation in this class. The python script is located at <ulink url="https://github.com/AXOTrack/disp-calc-python">AXOTrack repository</ulink>. <linebreak/>
Because of memory restrictions the implementation on the AXO X1 device could not transfer the complete acceleration data in one vector to the alorithm, instead the acceleration data is requested in small pieces from ADXL store task, so that the calculation can be performed sequentially. <linebreak/>
 See also message sequence chart in section <ref refid="_m_s_c_1SectionDisplacement" kindref="member">Displacement Calculation</ref>.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="remark"><para>This source code is confidential and proprietary information of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. You may not disclose, copy, or distribute this source code or any part thereof without the explicit permission of AXO Track GmbH, Berlin. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
